parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the accelerator pedal sensor can cause the vehicle to not move, even when the accelerator pedal is applied, leading to a very unsafe situation in traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle does not respond to accelerator pedal input
the car will not move
the accelerator pedal feels unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or shutting off without warning can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine shuts off or stalls without warning
the vehicle comes to a stop or slows down unexpectedly
the vehicle can be restarted immediately.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the headlights can reduce visibility, increase the risk of accidents, and compromise safety, especially at night.
symptoms: The headlights flash off or stay off when using the turn signals
the headlights turn off and stay off when completing a turn
the headlights can be restored by jogging the turn signal lever.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially if the vehicle accelerates while in park or drive gear.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without pressing the accelerator pedal
the engine RPM increases suddenly
the vehicle moves forward or backward without driver input
the brakes are engaged but the vehicle continues to move
the vehicle accelerates while in park or drive gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HECU unit can cause intermittent brake pedal to the floor issues, leading to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and a higher risk of accidents. Additionally, the failure can also cause brake binding, making the vehicle difficult to control.
symptoms: Intermittent brake pedal to the floor
reduced braking performance
increased stopping distances
brake binding
dashboard warning lights illuminating.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Carbon Buildup on Throttle Body
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive carbon buildup on the throttle body can cause the engine to stall without warning, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
the engine shuts off while driving
the vehicle experiences a sudden loss of power
the check engine warning light is illuminated.
